		<div id="comment_body_64125175">What a debacle this was! It&rsquo;s not *just* that Claudine Gay had an embarrassingly anemic publication record for a Harvard president, with much of it plagiarized and with much of what was plagiarized *not worth plagiarizing*. It&rsquo;s that so many scholars went on record defending the most egregious cases of plagiarism and her incredible mediocrity, so that everyone now has a clear view of Harvard&rsquo;s idea of &ldquo;merit.&rdquo; That can&rsquo;t be solved just by Claudine resigning. Now the rot is clear. The alleged prestige of Harvard, whatever was left of it, is now gone. There is probably more prestige to be had from graduating from Podunk Community College.</div>
